0
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Downloaded From www.AllSubs.org

1
00:01:14,808 --> 00:01:15,934
More blood!

2
00:01:15,975 --> 00:01:19,138
Great. Keep it coming.
Chuck, Terry, pump away.

3
00:01:19,179 --> 00:01:21,340
Don't be stingy.

4
00:01:21,381 --> 00:01:23,440
Watch that arm.
I can see that fake arm.

5
00:01:23,483 --> 00:01:25,246
Chase, keep that claw
really moving.

6
00:01:25,285 --> 00:01:27,276
Jeffrey, jam it on there
just like Freddy would.

7
00:01:27,320 --> 00:01:30,153
Good, good. And cut!
Print that, Gretchen.

8
00:01:34,961 --> 00:01:36,189
Chase, you're a genius.

9
00:01:36,229 --> 00:01:38,663
This makes his old claw look
like Mother Teresa's mitten.

10
00:01:38,698 --> 00:01:40,996
You better thank them.
They're very sensitive.

11
00:01:41,034 --> 00:01:43,002
Chuck, Terry, great blood.

12
00:01:43,036 --> 00:01:46,005
- Thank you very much.
- Some of our best work.

13
00:01:46,039 --> 00:01:47,904
Hey, monkey man,
want to see some neat stuff?

14
00:01:49,075 --> 00:01:50,702
Come on.

15
00:01:50,743 --> 00:01:52,108
It's only make-believe.

16
00:01:52,145 --> 00:01:54,306
Marianne, I gotta go.

17
00:01:59,719 --> 00:02:01,050
Low bridge.

18
00:02:03,990 --> 00:02:07,983
Let's see if we can
scare the P.J.'s off Mommy.

19
00:02:10,997 --> 00:02:12,259
Hey, Heather.

20
00:02:21,207 --> 00:02:22,504
You hungry, Dylan?

21
00:02:29,015 --> 00:02:30,539
Gotcha.

22
00:02:30,583 --> 00:02:33,074
It should have flexed more.

23
00:02:33,119 --> 00:02:35,781
I think the servos
got shorted out with blood.

24
00:02:35,822 --> 00:02:38,985
Well, take it apart,
pull it out...

25
00:02:39,025 --> 00:02:40,856
and insulate them
with some styro.

26
00:02:40,894 --> 00:02:42,919
The thing wasn't meant to be
submerged, for Pete's sake.

27
00:02:44,564 --> 00:02:46,122
I don't like that thing.

28
00:02:46,166 --> 00:02:47,827
That thing puts bread
on our table.

29
00:02:47,867 --> 00:02:49,858
Is it alive, Daddy?

30
00:02:49,903 --> 00:02:52,736
Heather,
you're in the next shot.

31
00:02:52,772 --> 00:02:56,003
State-of-the-art animatronics
with bio-organic grafting.

32
00:02:56,042 --> 00:02:59,273
Bull tendons, nerve bundles
from a live Doberman.

33
00:03:15,695 --> 00:03:18,664
Must've have picked up a signal
from an Eighties walkie-talkie.

34
00:03:18,698 --> 00:03:20,632
- Sure it's off?
- It's off.

35
00:03:20,667 --> 00:03:24,034
Funny, it's warm...
just like a real hand.

36
00:03:28,041 --> 00:03:29,565
Oh, God.

37
00:03:32,912 --> 00:03:35,278
What the hell's going on here?
Cut the effects!

38
00:03:42,088 --> 00:03:45,751
Terry, where is it? Terry!

39
00:03:45,792 --> 00:03:47,453
Chuck, get off me!

40
00:03:48,194 --> 00:03:49,923
Heather, where is it?

41
00:03:49,963 --> 00:03:51,760
Chase, where the hell is it?

42
00:03:56,436 --> 00:03:57,869
Come on.

43
00:04:04,944 --> 00:04:06,309
What the fuck?!

44
00:04:20,493 --> 00:04:21,983
Earthquake. Come on.

45
00:04:28,234 --> 00:04:30,202
Mommy!

46
00:05:02,001 --> 00:05:03,127
What is that?

47
00:05:04,037 --> 00:05:05,868
Car alarms.

48
00:05:08,875 --> 00:05:10,342
You OK?

49
00:05:13,613 --> 00:05:14,875
You OK, chief?

50
00:05:16,783 --> 00:05:18,250
Honey, do you have a fever?

51
00:05:18,284 --> 00:05:19,751
Just another earthquake, Dylan.

52
00:05:19,786 --> 00:05:21,447
Getting kind of fun, huh?

53
00:05:21,487 --> 00:05:23,921
Daddy. Blood.

54
00:05:23,956 --> 00:05:26,254
It's nothing, guys.

55
00:05:26,292 --> 00:05:29,125
It's a scratch. Really.

56
00:05:29,162 --> 00:05:30,789
Where did you get that?

57
00:05:30,830 --> 00:05:33,321
I don't know. Picture, I guess.

58
00:05:33,366 --> 00:05:35,834
When it fell. It's no big deal.

59
00:05:35,868 --> 00:05:37,927
Put a bandage on it.

60
00:05:37,970 --> 00:05:39,437
Don't worry about it.

61
00:05:47,847 --> 00:05:48,973
Geologists at Cal Tech...

62
00:05:49,015 --> 00:05:51,506
have confirmed
this morning's aftershock...

63
00:05:51,551 --> 00:05:53,075
Do we have to watch that?

64
00:05:53,119 --> 00:05:54,586
...five-point-three
on the Richter scale.

65
00:05:54,620 --> 00:05:55,746
Thought you turned it on.

66
00:05:55,788 --> 00:05:57,653
It was strong enough
to cause further collapse...

67
00:05:57,690 --> 00:06:00,124
of the already badly damaged
parking structure...

68
00:06:00,159 --> 00:06:01,990
I'll turn it off.

69
00:06:02,028 --> 00:06:04,428
Officials say
that this is normal...

70
00:06:04,464 --> 00:06:06,762
following a quake
of last week's magnitude...

71
00:06:06,799 --> 00:06:09,632
now thought to be a massive 6.8.

72
00:06:11,337 --> 00:06:14,602
Dylan, this is breakfast,
not arts and crafts.

73
00:06:16,476 --> 00:06:17,773
What?

74
00:06:17,810 --> 00:06:19,801
Did you get any sleep
last night?

75
00:06:19,846 --> 00:06:22,212
More or less.

76
00:06:22,248 --> 00:06:25,240
OK, time to get dressed.
I'm late.

77
00:06:25,284 --> 00:06:27,081
You going away?

78
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:29,486
Just for a few hours.
Julie will be with you.

79
00:06:35,661 --> 00:06:38,789
Is there anything other than
the obvious bothering you?

80
00:06:38,831 --> 00:06:41,425
I think five earthquakes
in three weeks is enough.

81
00:06:43,703 --> 00:06:45,330
Hasn't been another phone call,
has there?

82
00:06:47,707 --> 00:06:49,971
Good sign.

83
00:06:50,009 --> 00:06:53,410
Two full weeks without him.
Maybe he got hit by a truck.

84
00:06:53,446 --> 00:06:56,142
He's closer, if anything.

85
00:06:56,182 --> 00:06:58,707
It's giving me nightmares,
Chase.

86
00:06:59,752 --> 00:07:01,276
Did you have one last night?

87
00:07:03,055 --> 00:07:05,421
It's just the earthquakes,
Heather.

88
00:07:05,458 --> 00:07:06,948
Maybe.

89
00:07:08,094 --> 00:07:10,255
Maybe I shouldn't do
this interview today.

90
00:07:10,296 --> 00:07:15,495
No. You gotta get back
on the horse sometime.

91
00:07:15,535 --> 00:07:18,936
Look, you had a nut case
making harassing phone calls.

92
00:07:18,971 --> 00:07:20,438
I know how scary that's been.

93
00:07:20,473 --> 00:07:22,407
No, you don't.

94
00:07:23,976 --> 00:07:27,070
OK, I don't.

95
00:07:27,113 --> 00:07:29,581
But it doesn't mean
that it can't be over.

96
00:07:29,615 --> 00:07:31,378
But what if it isn't over?

97
00:07:33,653 --> 00:07:35,621
Maybe you should
tell me your dream.

98
00:07:37,323 --> 00:07:39,553
It was nothing. I was...

99
00:07:41,294 --> 00:07:44,263
You and I were working on
this movie, together for once...

100
00:07:44,297 --> 00:07:47,960
and one of your special effects
went really wrong.

101
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:52,437
And Chuck and Terry got hurt...

102
00:07:52,472 --> 00:07:53,666
and...

103
00:07:55,007 --> 00:07:56,907
Well, your fingers were cut.

104
00:07:56,943 --> 00:07:58,410
Right here?

105
00:08:01,848 --> 00:08:05,011
Heather, you were
probably half awake...

106
00:08:05,051 --> 00:08:07,110
and saw my fingers get nicked
when the mirror fell.

107
00:08:07,153 --> 00:08:08,848
Dreams are like that.

108
00:08:13,125 --> 00:08:17,027
Look, if you don't want me
to go on this job, I won't.

109
00:08:19,298 --> 00:08:21,129
Just be careful, OK?

110
00:08:21,167 --> 00:08:23,931
I think I can survive
two days in Palm Springs...

111
00:08:23,970 --> 00:08:26,939
supplying soap bubbles
for a detergent commercial.

112
00:08:26,973 --> 00:08:28,099
I guess so.

113
00:08:28,140 --> 00:08:29,402
You guess so?

114
00:08:30,243 --> 00:08:31,403
Come here.

115
00:08:41,153 --> 00:08:42,814
Forty-eight hours.

116
00:08:44,223 --> 00:08:45,986
I'll be back in no time.

117
00:08:46,993 --> 00:08:48,324
I gotta go.

118
00:08:57,670 --> 00:08:59,262
I love what you've done
with the place.

119
00:09:00,673 --> 00:09:01,935
Knock 'em dead.

120
00:09:05,578 --> 00:09:07,876
Dylan, I gotta go.
Take care of Mommy.

121
00:09:32,138 --> 00:09:33,969
Nancy.

122
00:09:41,414 --> 00:09:43,939
Dylan, I don't want you
watching this.

123
00:09:47,787 --> 00:09:49,948
Dylan, what's wrong?
What's wrong?!

124
00:09:49,989 --> 00:09:51,456
What's happening to you?

125
00:10:07,106 --> 00:10:09,438
One, two...

126
00:10:23,122 --> 00:10:24,521
Freddy's coming for you!

127
00:10:38,671 --> 00:10:41,401
Someone's coming.

128
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:42,600
What?

129
00:10:59,392 --> 00:11:00,791
Are you OK, honey?

130
00:11:18,778 --> 00:11:20,040
Is everything OK?

131
00:11:20,079 --> 00:11:23,071
It's just these quakes.
Did you feel one just now?

132
00:11:23,115 --> 00:11:25,982
No. A big truck went by
before you opened the door.

133
00:11:26,018 --> 00:11:27,815
It's life on the fault line.

134
00:11:27,853 --> 00:11:29,878
- Hey, tiger.
- Hi, Julie.

135
00:11:31,223 --> 00:11:34,522
Does he feel warm to you?
He had a fever this morning.

136
00:11:36,362 --> 00:11:37,795
No, he seems OK.

137
00:11:39,198 --> 00:11:40,995
Are you sure
that's all that's wrong?

138
00:11:44,070 --> 00:11:46,300
Leave us alone,
you son of a bitch!

139
00:11:46,338 --> 00:11:48,101
L.A. Limousine, ma'am.

140
00:11:48,140 --> 00:11:50,370
Just wanted you to know
I'm out front.

141
00:11:57,750 --> 00:12:00,150
I'm sorry.
Can you hang on a minute?

142
00:12:10,663 --> 00:12:12,096
What is it?

143
00:12:12,131 --> 00:12:13,291
I don't know.

144
00:12:14,767 --> 00:12:16,894
I just have
this weird feeling today.

145
00:12:16,936 --> 00:12:20,099
Mommy? Stay home, then.

146
00:12:26,712 --> 00:12:28,577
This damn caller.

147
00:12:31,283 --> 00:12:32,580
He's started again?

148
00:12:34,186 --> 00:12:35,983
Sick fuck.

149
00:12:37,123 --> 00:12:38,283
Sorry.

150
00:12:40,226 --> 00:12:43,252
Dylan doesn't seem
to have a fever.

151
00:12:43,295 --> 00:12:45,763
It's probably just your nerves.

152
00:12:45,798 --> 00:12:47,356
Nerves?

153
00:12:48,501 --> 00:12:51,402
I just meant from the shaker
this morning.

154
00:12:51,437 --> 00:12:53,735
Everybody's freaked out about
how many we've been having.

155
00:12:53,773 --> 00:12:55,434
And then these phone calls.

156
00:13:00,346 --> 00:13:01,608
Don't answer it.

157
00:13:10,656 --> 00:13:14,114
Excuse me, ma'am,
but we are going to be late.

158
00:13:25,938 --> 00:13:30,375
Dylan, I gotta go. Forgive me?

159
00:13:30,409 --> 00:13:31,740
Bye.

160
00:13:46,192 --> 00:13:47,989
I'll call the cops for you.

161
00:13:48,027 --> 00:13:49,324
You've got the number
on the fridge, right?

162
00:13:49,361 --> 00:13:50,953
Give them
the time they called...

163
00:13:50,996 --> 00:13:53,590
and they're keeping this list,
supposedly.

164
00:13:53,632 --> 00:13:56,328
Julie, I'm really sorry.

165
00:13:56,368 --> 00:13:58,336
My nerves are
a little raw these days.

166
00:13:58,370 --> 00:13:59,530
It's OK.

167
00:14:06,812 --> 00:14:08,177
Yeah. I gotta go.

168
00:14:08,214 --> 00:14:10,239
- Morning.
- Good morning.

169
00:14:25,731 --> 00:14:26,959
You played that girl.

170
00:14:28,634 --> 00:14:30,499
In that movie.

171
00:14:30,536 --> 00:14:32,060
With the guy with the...

172
00:14:33,205 --> 00:14:36,265
Yeah, sure. That's you.

173
00:14:36,308 --> 00:14:38,503
That's what I love
about this job.

174
00:14:38,544 --> 00:14:40,205
I get to meet the stars.

175
00:14:40,246 --> 00:14:42,339
I'm hardly a star.

176
00:14:42,381 --> 00:14:44,144
What, are you kidding?

177
00:14:44,183 --> 00:14:46,310
I love your stuff.

178
00:14:47,553 --> 00:14:49,020
The first was the best.

179
00:14:49,622 --> 00:14:52,682
Where the girlfriend's cut open
and dragged across the ceiling.

180
00:14:52,725 --> 00:14:53,851
It was awesome.

181
00:14:53,893 --> 00:14:57,852
And when all that blood comes
out of your boyfriend's bed?

182
00:14:57,897 --> 00:14:59,728
I thought I'd shit.

183
00:14:59,765 --> 00:15:02,393
But they never should
have killed off Freddy.

184
00:15:03,502 --> 00:15:05,163
Heather, look, we gotta go.

185
00:15:05,204 --> 00:15:08,696
Cutting it close, aren't you?
You trying to get me fired?

186
00:15:08,741 --> 00:15:10,265
OK! We're coming!

187
00:15:13,045 --> 00:15:16,105
So, Heather, we're approaching
the tenth anniversary...

188
00:15:16,148 --> 00:15:17,775
of this whole
"Nightmare on Elm Street" thing.

189
00:15:17,816 --> 00:15:21,274
I mean, the original,
five very popular sequels.

190
00:15:21,320 --> 00:15:25,381
How has all the success
affected you personally?

191
00:15:26,458 --> 00:15:29,052
I don't know
if it really has, Sam.

192
00:15:29,094 --> 00:15:31,324
God. With the exception
of One and Three...

193
00:15:31,363 --> 00:15:33,194
I pretty much stayed out of it.

194
00:15:33,232 --> 00:15:35,325
Well, I'm doing a lot more
television now...

195
00:15:35,367 --> 00:15:37,232
so those hours
let me spend a lot more time...

196
00:15:37,269 --> 00:15:38,600
with my husband
and my little boy.

197
00:15:38,637 --> 00:15:40,935
You have a little boy.
What's his name?

198
00:15:42,141 --> 00:15:43,267
Dylan.

199
00:15:43,309 --> 00:15:46,005
With Dylan,
does that change your feeling...

200
00:15:46,045 --> 00:15:48,275
your perspective
about horror movies?

201
00:15:48,314 --> 00:15:50,009
No, not really.

202
00:15:50,049 --> 00:15:51,983
Would you let him
see one of your movies?

203
00:15:52,017 --> 00:15:54,110
My son? No.

204
00:15:54,153 --> 00:15:56,519
I'm sure people ask you this
all the time...

205
00:15:56,555 --> 00:15:58,921
Is there going
to be another sequel...

206
00:15:58,958 --> 00:16:02,655
and what's more,
is Freddy really dead?

207
00:16:02,695 --> 00:16:05,391
Of course he is.
Freddy's dead and gone.

208
00:16:05,431 --> 00:16:09,094
And how about your costar
in the original...

209
00:16:09,134 --> 00:16:11,534
would you trust him
alone with Dylan?

210
00:16:11,570 --> 00:16:14,266
Robert? I don't know.

211
00:16:14,306 --> 00:16:16,501
Why don't we ask him
how he'd feel about it?

212
00:16:16,542 --> 00:16:20,000
We've got a big surprise for you
and for our audience.

213
00:16:20,045 --> 00:16:22,070
Let's bring him out.
He is the best of the bad.

214
00:16:22,114 --> 00:16:25,140
Let's say hello
to Robert Englund.

215
00:16:34,660 --> 00:16:36,992
Love ya, babe!

216
00:16:37,029 --> 00:16:38,587
We'll do lunch!

217
00:16:42,234 --> 00:16:45,328
I'm alive once again!

218
00:16:45,371 --> 00:16:49,603
Freddy's back! Give it up
for your Uncle Freddy!

219
00:16:50,843 --> 00:16:54,301
Just when you thought it was
safe to get back into bed!

220
00:16:57,816 --> 00:16:59,113
Give me five!

221
00:17:03,555 --> 00:17:07,355
I'm back,
and I'm badder than ever!

222
00:17:11,263 --> 00:17:14,994
You are all my children now!

223
00:17:21,540 --> 00:17:22,871
I got to go, Robert.

224
00:17:22,908 --> 00:17:25,536
Just a second. I'll walk you.

225
00:17:25,577 --> 00:17:27,067
There you go, kids.

226
00:17:27,112 --> 00:17:28,739
- Thank you.
- Bye-bye.

227
00:17:30,115 --> 00:17:32,140
- You OK?
- I'm fine.

228
00:17:32,184 --> 00:17:34,744
Well, everything went great,
I thought.

229
00:17:34,787 --> 00:17:36,516
We really got you, didn't we?

230
00:17:36,555 --> 00:17:38,523
I don't know why
you didn't tell me.

231
00:17:38,557 --> 00:17:41,856
Come on. They loved
the expression on your face.

232
00:17:41,894 --> 00:17:43,384
I think they'd like
to see us together again.

233
00:17:43,429 --> 00:17:45,488
In what, a romantic comedy?

234
00:17:45,531 --> 00:17:46,998
Just because
it's a love story...

235
00:17:47,032 --> 00:17:50,058
doesn't mean you can't
have a decapitation or two.

236
00:17:50,102 --> 00:17:53,094
- There's a call for you.
- For me?

237
00:17:53,138 --> 00:17:54,628
I'll talk to you later.

238
00:17:57,743 --> 00:18:00,803
Heather, it's Sara Risher
over at New Line Cinema.

239
00:18:00,846 --> 00:18:02,177
How are you?

240
00:18:02,214 --> 00:18:04,944
How are you?
This is a voice from the past.

241
00:18:04,983 --> 00:18:06,109
It sure is.

242
00:18:06,151 --> 00:18:08,312
Listen, Heather,
I won't take but a minute.

243
00:18:08,353 --> 00:18:10,787
It's just that we have
something to propose to you...

244
00:18:10,823 --> 00:18:12,916
and I wonder
if you'd stop by the offices.

245
00:18:12,958 --> 00:18:14,858
Bob would love to talk to you.

246
00:18:14,893 --> 00:18:16,087
Sure. When?

247
00:18:16,128 --> 00:18:18,790
No time like the present.
The car will bring you over.

248
00:18:18,831 --> 00:18:20,594
- Now?
- Just take a minute.

249
00:18:20,632 --> 00:18:23,226
You'll be glad you did, I bet.
Bye.

250
00:18:47,793 --> 00:18:50,523
- Can I help you?
- I'm here to see Bob Shaye.

251
00:18:50,562 --> 00:18:52,189
Was Bob expecting you?

252
00:18:53,899 --> 00:18:55,196
Sara. How are you?

253
00:18:55,234 --> 00:18:57,600
- I'm fine. How are you?
- Great to see you.

254
00:18:57,636 --> 00:18:59,604
- You look great.
- Thank you.

255
00:18:59,638 --> 00:19:02,801
Bob is dying to see you.
Can I get you something?

256
00:19:02,841 --> 00:19:04,536
- Coffee would be fine.
- Black?

257
00:19:04,576 --> 00:19:06,635
- Black's fine.
- Could you get us some coffee?

258
